						               													<description>Lotta and her friends have to catch Cheyenne's rabbits which escaped. The top of the variable game board shows five characters from the book series, the bottom shows five locations. In between there is a labyrinth consisting of four stripes with paths on them. &amp;#10;One player rolls a dice, determining from which of the characters a rabbit escaped. All players follow the path of the rabbit and try to determine which location it is hiding in. Rabbits always turn when they have the chance, and if the stripe shows two rabbit holes, they change from one to the other. When a player thinks they know where the rabbit is, they grab the corresponding location tile first. If successful, they get to keep one of the stripes which is then replaced by another. Tiles that have been used are returned face down, so a memory aspect is added. When all stripes have been dealt out, the player with most stripes wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
